{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-3970].
  {panel}

Much like confluence, and other foruming software, it's nice to be able to login to an application and see what has changed since you've been there last.

I was thinking in the Issue navigator, in the Dates and Times section, there could be a checkbox that plainly says " Created/Modified Since Last Login".  It would be great if this was fine-grained enough to appreciate the difference between 9am and 3pm on any given day.  Which is why I didn't suggest a re-use of existing fields, which (aside from hard coded values in the drop-downs) seem limited to dates only?

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-3953].
  {panel}

Add another option view to the Issue Navigator to give Issues in jelly tags so that you can take it and import into another JIRA instance.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-3949].
  {panel}

The project summary page includes a section listing the number of "open" issues for each priority and assignee. The issues that Jira consider "open" is currently hard-coded as those with a status of "Open", "Reopened" and "In Progress". I would like to include "Resolved" in this, but beyond editing the source code it is not currently possible to do this.

With configurable workflow (JRA-2580) and the ability to create extra issues statuses, the configuration of what is considered "open" will become even more important.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-3935].
  {panel}

I'd like to have a daily email or report listing all the changes in JIRA issues -- creation, modification, commented, etc.

Confluence has this and it's great -- if that was exactly what we had in JIRA we would be thrilled.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-3933].
  {panel}

It would be really helpful to be able to populate custom mail headers in the email notifications.

We'd like to populate two custom headers, say, X-JIRA-PROJECT and X-JIRA-ISSUE with the project and the issue number.  Then our mail clients could sort and group by those two header fields. Possibly we'd also want to add priority or custom fields into these headers.

Another option would be to fill in the In-Response-To header so that messages thread properly, but I'm not sure if that would work as well.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-3910].
  {panel}

Our managers need to see issues they reported with assignees detailed on their dashboard.

How can we set up this?

Looks like either a new portlet needed, or set of fields shown for user filters should be customized.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-3901].
  {panel}

Need to select which groups will newly created users be added to by default, and separate this from the Global 'JIRA Users' Permission to avoid confusion.
